translated: Ljunggren, Harald, provincial physician, Gothenburg, b. 21/5/98 in Strömstad to minister Ernst Teofron L. and Eva Isabella Kuhgren. Married on 25/xx [year] to Eva Maria Hagberg. Children: Lars b. 26 [year], Ingrid b. 28, Karin b. 32. Education: High school diploma in Uddevalla in 1916, Bachelor of Medicine in Uppsala in 1919, Medical Licentiate in 1924. Temporary assistant at the Pathology Institute in Uppsala from 1920-1922, assistant there from 1921-1922, assistant doctor and temporary deputy doctor at Örebro Hospital from 1924-1925 and for five months in 1925-1927, appointed as city doctor in Trollhättan, provincial doctor in Tjörn, Eskilstuna, Åseda, Fjugesta, Uddeholm, Jörn, Norsjö, and Sjöbo districts from 1924-1927, deputy doctor at Svenshögen sanatorium from 1926-1927, acting senior doctor for three months, deputy doctor at Norrtälje Hospital from 1928-1929, city doctor in Hjo from 1929-1939, provincial doctor in Öckerö district since 1931.
